svg.title: Clouds of the genera Stratocumulus, Stratus, Cumulus and Cumulonimbus: Cumulus mediocris or congestus, with or without cumulus of species fractus or humilis or stratocumulus, all having their bases at the same level
svg.desc: WMO international weather symbol: Clouds of the genera Stratocumulus, Stratus, Cumulus and Cumulonimbus: Cumulus of moderate or strong vertical extent, generally with protuberances in the form of domes or towers, either accompanied or not by other cumulus or by stratocumulus, all having their bases at the same level
